Albizia chinensis

   [2959.jpg]
   Authority (Osbeck) Merr.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
   Synonyms Acacia lomatocarpa DC., Acacia stipulata DC., Albizia
   marginata (Lamk.) Merr., Albizia stipulata (DC.) Boivin, Arthrosprion
   stipulatum (DC.) Hassk., Mimosa chinensis, Mimosa marginata Lamk.,
   Mimosa smithiana Roxb., Mimosa stipulacea Roxb.
   Common names Chinese albizia, tamaligi
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 2959

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   An almost evergreen tree reaching a height of up to 30 m, while the
   trunk may reach a diameter of 1-2 m.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial.
   COMMON NAMES
   Karai.
   FURTHER INF
   Karai is native of Southeast Asia, Bangladesh and Myanmar. It can be
   found at elevations between sea level and 1300 m. The tree is adapted
   to conditions similar to Albizia falcataria and will also withstand
   poorer sites. It is more windfirm than A. falcataria. The tree can fix
   nitrogen. On good sites yield may be 10-12 m3/ha/year. It has been
   mentioned as a potential agroforestry species.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Zabala N 1990 pp 3-5 [TEMP, RAIN, LIG, FER, DRA, USE]

